<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> good at something • good on something • good with something</xh5><p> <i>good at something—</i>proficient in a subject or an activity: Boys and girls rate themselves as being equally <u>good at science</u> at the primary-school level.</p><p> <i>good on something—</i>skilful in one’s performance on a musical instrument: Hayes said that Pearl was “quite <u>good” on</u> the violin and also proficient on the mandolin.</p><p> <i>good with something—</i>competent in the use of smth.: He was very <u>good with</u> horses—he worked with them so that they trusted and respected him.</p> </entry>
